sl-Castle-20x30.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/01134903\/Litomysl-Castle.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-9-trosky-castle\"><strong>9. Trosky Castle<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Wow. Trosky Castle will take your breath away; it is the clear winner for &#x2018;the most unique setting&#x2019; of all the Czech castles. The two towers of the castle are perched on the peaks of two volcanic plugs that can be seen for miles across the landscapes of Cesky Raj. Connecting stairs join the towers to the main part of the castle below, so prepare to climb a few stairs on your trip to Trosky Castle!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Because of its unusual position, it&#x2019;s one of the traveler&#x2019;s must-see sights in the Czech Republic, and it&#x2019;s very popular for adventurers who want to bike or hike up the hills and rocks to visit the castle.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--tip \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--tip\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">Did you know?<\/strong> There are rumored to be a network of cellars and underground tunnels beneath the volcanic rock<\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div><